hopobject.body: Have you got a current driving licence? summahealth.org/dreamhouse This November 15, Sony will release its new PlayStation 4 for $399.99. Seven days later, Microsoft will release its $499.99 Xbox One. As we are going to press, no one outside Sony and Microsoft has been able to play with either, although there have been plenty of sexy demos and a lot of promises made. Indeed, both Xbox One and PS4 preorders are currently sold out. The demand is there. But which should I choose? More importantly, which should you choose?
